headline: White House considers antitrust probe into homebuilders, Bloomberg News reports
summary: Feb 6 (Reuters) - Trump administration officials are exploring opening an antitrust investigation into U.S. homebuilders as the White House ramps up efforts to address the housing affordability crisis

headline: Homebuilder stocks fall after potential antitrust probe report
summary: Investing.com -- Shares of major U.S. homebuilders fell Friday following a Bloomberg report that the White House is considering launching an antitrust investigation into the industry amid concerns about housing affordability.

headline: A Key Takeaway From Earnings Season: Signs of Consumer Weakness
summary: Earnings season is more than halfway over, and a clear laggard is emerging: companies that sell non-essential items to consumers.  A high ratio of companies—38%—have also missed consensus earnings forecasts.  The sector covers a broad swathe of the economy, encompassing a range of companies from Amazon and DoorDash to Tractor Supply and Marriott.
